\section{\texorpdfstring{Wording
Changes\hyperref[wording-changes]{}}{Wording Changes}}\label{wording-changes}

Large changes are \VERB|\OperatorTok{:::}\NormalTok{ add}| for
additions, \VERB|\OperatorTok{:::}\NormalTok{ rm}| for removals.

\begin{quote}
Modify section {28.5.5 Formatting functions
\href{https://eel.is/c++draft/format.functions}{{[}format.functions{]}}}:

{\color[HTML]{006e28}

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\NormalTok{template\textless{}class... Args\textgreater{}}
\NormalTok{  string format(const locale\& loc, string\_view fmt, const Args\&... args);}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}

\emph{Returns:}
\VERB|\NormalTok{vformat(loc, fmt, make\_format\_args(args...))}|.}
\end{quote}

Small, inline changes are done with
\VERB|\NormalTok{[new text]\{.add\}}| or
\VERB|\NormalTok{[old text]\{.rm\}}|.

Substitutions can be written as
\VERB|\NormalTok{[old text](new text)\{.sub\}}|. This is essentially
just a short-form for
\VERB|\NormalTok{[old text]\{.rm\}[new text]\{.add\}}|.

The optional \emph{attribute-specifier-seq} appertains to the
{{{\color[HTML]{bf0303}\sout{label}}}{{\color[HTML]{006e28}\uline{\emph{general-label}}}}}.
The only use of a {{{\color[HTML]{bf0303}\sout{label with an
\emph{identifier}}}}{{\color[HTML]{006e28}\uline{\emph{label}}}}} is as
the target of a \VERB|\ControlFlowTok{goto}|,
{{\color[HTML]{006e28}\uline{\VERB|\NormalTok{break}|, or
\VERB|\NormalTok{continue}|}}}. No two
{{{\color[HTML]{bf0303}\sout{label}}}{{\color[HTML]{006e28}\uline{\emph{label}}}}}s
in a function shall have the same \emph{identifier}. A
{{{\color[HTML]{bf0303}\sout{label}}}{{\color[HTML]{006e28}\uline{\emph{general-label}}}}}
can be used {{\color[HTML]{bf0303}\sout{in a \VERB|\NormalTok{goto}|
statement}}} before its introduction by a \emph{labeled-statement}.

